The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 18: Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) has teamed up with China National Petroleum Corporation (CNPC) to win a gas block in Peru, expanding its presence in Latin America.Reliance Exploration and Production DMCC along with CNPC and Argentinas Pluspetrol have won the rights to explore for gas in block 155, in Puno, next to the border with Bolivia.                            
	 London, Sept. 18: A consortium of major European steel companies, ULCOS, which includes ArcelorMittal and Corus, will collaborate with worlds leading mining firm Rio Tinto for the Isarna project. The project is aimed at developing an environment-friendly iron making process.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 18: Bhel will double its manufacturing capacity to 20,000MW by 2011 from 10,000MW now. Bhel expected to increase its capacity to 15,000MW by the year-end.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 18: Marks amp; Spencer Reliance will open its first store in Mumbai in January 2009, Marks amp; Spencer CEO (India), Mark Ashman, said.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 18: The State Bank of India (SBI) plans to offer credit products through its no-frills accounts to make its financial inclusion operations more viable, SBI chief general manager Shyamal Acharya said.                                                                                                                          
